    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item reveal">
        <button class="faq-question">How is this different from Angi or HomeAdvisor?</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Angi sells the same lead to multiple contractors — you're paying for a chance, not a customer. With your own website, when someone finds you on Google, they're calling you and only you. No competition. No bidding wars. Plus, the content we create keeps working forever. You're building an asset, not renting access.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item reveal">
        <button class="faq-question">How long before I see results?</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>SEO isn't instant — anyone who tells you otherwise is lying. Most contractors start seeing meaningful traffic growth in 3–6 months. By month 12, you should be getting consistent leads from search. It's slower than buying ads, but those leads are free once you're ranking.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item reveal">
        <button class="faq-question">What if I already have a website?</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Depends on what you have. If it's decent, we might be able to work with it and just add content. If it's a mess (or built on some platform that's impossible to update), it might make more sense to start fresh. I'll tell you straight up what I think — no upselling just to make a bigger sale.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item reveal">
        <button class="faq-question">Do I have to sign a contract?</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. The website build is a one-time payment. The monthly content plans are month-to-month. You can cancel anytime with 30 days notice. I'd rather earn your business every month than lock you into something you can't get out of.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item reveal">
        <button class="faq-question">What do I actually own?</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Everything. Your domain name is yours (I'll help you set it up if you don't have one). All the content we write is yours. If you ever leave, you take everything with you. I don't hold anything hostage.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item reveal">
        <button class="faq-question">Can I just get the website without the monthly content?</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Absolutely. Some contractors just want a professional site and plan to handle content themselves (or just don't want it). That's fine. The website builds are standalone — no strings attached.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

